cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Two world records in Grassmannian coherence packings (d=4, n=64) hlc"
message: "If you use these records or this work, please cite as below."
type: dataset
authors:
  - family-names: "Amichis Luengo"
    given-names: "Rafael"
    affiliation: "Independent researcher, Madrid, Spain"
date-released: 2026-05-12
version: "1.0"
url: "https://github.com/tretoef-estrella/sloane-coherence-records"
abstract: >
  Two world records in the minimum-coherence packing of 64 unit vectors in
  complex 4-dimensional space (Grassmannian coherence packing problem,
  cell d=4, n=64, holographic-line case "hlc") were established on
  May 12, 2026. The previous record (Cohn et al., coherence
  0.687160201509307) had stood for over a decade. The first new record
  (coherence 0.687040494471422, gap -1.197e-04 vs. Cohn) was obtained in
  the afternoon. The second record (coherence 0.687035170223597, gap
  -1.250e-04 vs. Cohn, i.e. an improvement of 0.0182%) was obtained the
  same evening from a structurally distinct basin. Both packings were
  verified byte-exact by five independent kernels and an independent
  Python verifier (included in this repository). The work was carried out
  on a Mac M2 single-threaded at 25% CPU, in collaboration with the AI
  assistant Claude (Anthropic), using a novel optimisation paradigm
  combining Riemannian gradient flow over a smoothed-max coherence loss
  with a structure-aware warmstart strategy.
keywords:
  - Grassmannian packing
  - coherence
  - frame theory
  - equiangular tight frame
  - compressed sensing
  - MIMO precoding
  - CDMA codes
  - quantum state tomography
license: MIT

